The only question that really matters is whether this is cheaper than building new power lines. While you are saving on the costs of constructing new pylons you still have the cost of replacing the wires. The other disadvantage is that you only end up with twice the original transmission capacity instead of three times it if you built new and you have to follow existing routes while new lines can go between places that that power needs to be transmitted which are likely different now since new, renewable p<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64517803">

